  "slug": "forfar-bridie",
  "title": "Forfar Bridie",
  "subtitle": "A Scottish hand pie of seasoned beef and onion folded into a half-moon pastry",
  "excerpt": "The Forfar bridie is a Scottish savoury pasty: seasoned beef mince and onion enclosed in a rough hot water crust pastry folded into a half-moon and crimped on top, not along the side as with a Cornish pasty. It is a lunch-box staple from Angus.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional Scottish baking from Forfar, Angus. F. Marian McNeill, The Scots Kitchen (1929): bridie recipe with suet pastry. Traditional Scots hand-pie practice, Tayside region.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "bridie",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr49v200008sv4s7dfwt5d"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " is a Scottish hand pie: raw seasoned beef and onion folded into shortcrust pastry, crimped along the top of the curved edge, and baked hot until deeply golden. No potato, no carrot. The filling stays simple so the beef and pastry carry the dish.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The traditional pastry was made with suet; shortcrust is an acceptable modern substitute. The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "horseshoe crimp",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr49vu00018sv4hja953xp"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " takes practice but is not structurally necessary. A firm fork-pressed edge seals equally well.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Shortcrust pastry",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 500,
              "prepNote": "shop-bought or homemade, chilled",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp5mo25j000gwwv4vz7dp67m",
              "ingredientSlug": "shortcrust-pastry"
            },
            {
              "name": "Beef mince",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 400,
              "prepNote": "20% fat, or diced beef skirt",
              "groupLabel": "For the filling",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3y7001srkv4gz83wnhd",
              "ingredientSlug": "beef-mince"
            },
            {
              "name": "Onion",
              "unit": "each",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "very finely chopped",
              "groupLabel": "For the filling",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f59k0042rkv4afimm5ox",
              "ingredientSlug": "onion"
            },
            {
              "name": "Sea salt flakes",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": "For the filling",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7ll0087rkv43k6j3dft",
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-flakes"
            },
            {
              "name": "Black pepper",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "coarsely ground",
              "groupLabel": "For the filling",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7mq0089rkv49t6gtibv",
              "ingredientSlug": "black-pepper"
            },
            {
              "name": "Worcestershire sauce",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": "For the filling",
              "isOptional": true,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f8ss00acrkv46ion4ngo",
              "ingredientSlug": "worcestershire-sauce"
            },
            {
              "name": "Eggs",
              "unit": "each",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "beaten, for the egg wash",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3wj001prkv40f7svjvg",
              "ingredientSlug": "eggs"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mix the {{beef-mince}} with the {{onion}}, {{sea-salt-flakes}}, {{black-pepper}}, and Worcestershire sauce if using. The filling must be raw when it goes into the pastry. Do not add stock or egg; the natural juices are sufficient.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and crimp",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide the {{shortcrust-pastry}} into 4 equal pieces. Roll each into a rough oval about 22 cm long and 3 to 4 mm thick.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Place a quarter of the filling on one half of each oval, leaving a 2 cm border. Moisten the border with water.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Fold the empty half over the filling to form a half-moon and press the edges firmly together. Crimp with a fork along the curved top edge. Chill for 30 minutes on a lined baking tray.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C (180°C fan). Brush the bridies with beaten egg. Make a small steam vent in the top of each.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until deeply golden. Rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "rows": [
            {
              "fix": "Press and crimp firmly; moisten the edges before joining. Leave a 2 cm unfilled border.",
              "cause": "Edge not sealed firmly enough, or too much filling used",
              "symptom": "Juices leak from the seam during baking"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use mince with at least 20% fat. Pull the bridies at 40 minutes.",
              "cause": "Beef mince was too lean, or overbaked",
              "symptom": "Filling is dry inside"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check with an oven thermometer. Brush with undiluted beaten egg before baking.",
              "cause": "Oven temperature lower than expected",
              "symptom": "Pastry is pale"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Roll to size without pulling; stretched pastry always springs back in the oven.",
              "cause": "Pastry was stretched rather than rolled to size",
              "symptom": "Pastry shrinks and uncovers the filling"
            }
          ]
        },
        "content": []
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Forfar bridies come from the town of Forfar in Angus, Scotland, where they have been sold by bakers since at least the 1850s. They remain a staple in Scottish baker's shops and butchers, and are a regional counterpart to the English pasty tradition. Eaten hot from the oven or cold for a packed lunch, they need nothing alongside.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "glossaryTerms": [],
